[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating ClassLoader behavior**\n\nI'm exploring the use of `Class.forName(DEFAULT_IMPL_CLASSNAME)` in the Configurator class. It loads fine as it uses the Configurator's class loader. I'm curious about how ServiceLoader works with a custom ClassLoader that has no parent; could it load service classes? Maybe there’s a potential issue if the parent is null. I think modifying to use a ClassLoader denying all resources could help clarify functionality. I also wonder if ServiceLoader needs to load the provider class at all. Let's examine that situation more deeply.\n\n**Considering test class ordering**\n\nI'm thinking about whether I need to reset the `defaultImpl` if it’s already set; that might be tricky. Testing the order is essential, though. Should I create a method for testing and use `@TestClassOrder`? Hmm, that doesn't seem right. Maybe using `@TestMethodOrder` is an option, but I'm not sure. I wonder if I can get the JUnit engine to prioritize test classes by naming conventions. If I name a file like \"AaaaServerEndpoint,\" could that work? It certainly seems worth exploring!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_08469396b1f069470169f0e3e1a1048196b44a8323c2e2b1cf\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8OQG2YdedSRf4_yvTeXqXhp_PMbBUIXh1rdcbz8eOaymrsF6wtax-EYXf4ok1361f74xTU-9fbjERcSvTsEa8j4xbA3taVK7EUbrEXQfqTJ88ifvG4hiwA8Y1lH75i7ydGah_QFSzrBRDHEnNlavsgOTCD486Hi7tW8Lg4VKek8yMEFDSEyiOm-X5WMXN9SHciDLJd1GFeLdqk6QoYjfxd0xBWdpMsh1iisn16oVI_0UNG2O2Takb6_IQztukWzDgks5uOoJDmVB3O8yOu4MajpTq5qo0XmeYCWQR-73M-7zExgZQNpMVvK3d6Q4XWocgVkpJMH8B0i7f12nLz4DLdWeLb9In2jyMFKIv1NX4SGKLWkRjTPG4CHkKnxh412ohKIcSnGNn5jv2dYwOWkAT0KOLYIAqGNs0mAiN2nk14iBnZRmnSNnQ8IObI-nqrApfT8Ym-yqDtSiFw9f_5c7k8JLMlHLStdDpHZ1YyrK_g294_2NwCSiquWivy_HpQ-zcdpfVtklUqqo2xrj6U3Vc-IzvohCx-641qPuXCrNZv2E8Mv20kYFBqoeADWothTgCFxX491zXWIE35KcvO9Y35RCRc386tYDeobEFMkyXPZ-9oBoIKc_FaZmFvxab3cgUCtVH